on medicine","body":"Jane Minot Revere was a granddaughter of Paul Revere and daughter of the copper magnate Joseph Warren Revere. Her 1859 marriage to Dr. John Phillips Reynolds braided the Revere line into three generations of Boston physicians."},{"number":2,"category":"legacy","header":"Her son bought back the Revere house","body":"Among Jane’s eight children was John Phillips Reynolds Jr., who in 1902 purchased and preserved her grandfather’s house in Boston’s North End. The Revere ancestry she carried became the cause that defined his life."},{"number":3,"category":"family","header":"Her name carried two Boston dynasties","body":"Jane Minot Revere bore the names of two old Boston families, the Minots and the Reveres, at the moment they joined the medical Reynoldses. Her children’s names, Paul Revere Reynolds and Mary Robbins Reynolds among them, kept the ancestry deliberately visible."}],"slug":"jane-minot-revere-1835"}},"burialCemetery":null,"institutionsById":{},"crossConnections":[]}